<HEAD>Belgian Diplomat Reported Shot</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS thruout with Belgian Embassy correcting date of
shooting to Sunday sted Monday, ADDS location of incident, details
on robbery. No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman wounded a Belgian diplomat
and killed a woman companion in an apparent robbery attempt at a
resort south of Manila, the Belgian Embassy said Tuesday.
   Spokeswoman Marie Louise Vanherk said Benoit Standaert suffered
two gunshot wounds in the incident, which occurred Sunday, and was
in stable condition at a suburban Manila hospital. She said his
companion, Adorata Capistrano, died of her wounds.
   Ms. Vanherk quoted police in nearby Batangas province as saying
they suspected robbery was the motive because the gunman fled with
Ms. Capistrano's purse. The incident occurred at Lake Taal, 35
miles south of Manila, the spokeswoman said.
   The daily newspaper Tempo identified Standaert as the second
secretary of the Belgian Embassy in Manila. Newspapers earlier had
reported the shooting took place Monday.
