<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--MarathonTVWatcher     07-25 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Marathon TV Watcher,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Unemployed Carpenter Claims World Record For Television Watching</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 24-year-old unemployed carpenter
claimed a world record for continuous television watching today
after spending 168 hours gazing at the small screen.
   ``Most of the shows were pretty good. In fact, I could have gone
on for days and days,'' said David Woods, who completed his record
attempt in a box 20 yards above one of Sydney's busiest
thoroughfares.
   The Sydney man said a masseur and an electric nerve stimulator
helped him keep alert during the marathon stint.
   Woods, who was filmed by an Australian television show that
concentrates of wierd and wacky achievements, said after the
weeklong marathon effort that television programs ``really aren't
that bad.''
   The Guinness Book of Records does not list a current record for
television watching.
</TEXT>
