<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Fatal Plunge,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Falls To His Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 25-year-old man who apparently thought his
girlfriend was refusing to answer her door tried to enter from a
window ledge and fell seven stories to his death, police said.
   But neither the girl nor her father, with whom she lived, was
home at the time, said Sgt. Michael Chasen.
   He said the victim, Robert Jenkins, quarreled with his
girlfriend earlier in the day Sunday.
   ``So he went up to the apartment and, we think, he knocked on
the door and when he got no answer figured she was trying to avoid
him,'' Chasen said. ``So he tried to be sneaky.''
   Chasen said Jenkins crawled out on a narrow ledge and tried to
get to a window of his girlfriend's apartment, but fell into a
parking lot, landing near a car and setting off the auto's theft
alarm.
   A building custodian heard the alarm and called police.
 
