<2ND_LINE>PM-Indonesia-Quake,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Severe Earthquake Detected Off Indonesia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A severe earthquake registering 6.8 on the
Richter scale was detected today in the eastern Banda Sea off
Indonesia, the Royal Hong Kong Observatory reported.
   An observatory said in a statement that the center of the quake
was about 1,816 miles east of the Indonesian capital of Jakarta.
   A spokesman said the quake was recorded at 2:53 p.m. (2:53 a.m.
EDT) but that no other details were available.
   The Richter scale measures the total magnitude of an earthquake.
Every increase of one digit in the scale represents a 10-fold
increase in intensity.
   An earthquake registering 6 on the scale can cause severe damage
in populated areas.
