<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Sextuplets,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sextuplets Born In West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AACHEN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German woman give birth to
sextuplets and the four girls and two boys are in critical
condition, a university hospital spokeswoman said today.
   She said the babies, weighing between 1 pound, 6 ounces and 2
pounds, 2 ounces), have been placed in incubators.
   The sextuplets were born Sunday by Caesarean section operation
in the 27th week of pregnancy, said the hospital spokeswoman, who
spoke on condition of anonymity. A full-term pregnancy is 40 weeks.
   The spokeswoman declined to provide the names of the parents.
The Hamburg-based Bild newspaper reported the babies were born to
34-year-old Barbara Coenen and her husband Wilhelm, a 36-year-old
construction worker.
   Bild said the couple have two other children and that Mrs.
Coenen had taken fertility drugs.
</TEXT>
