<1ST_LINE>d p PM-BRF--MissingManager     07-25 0188</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Missing Manager,0195</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Candidate Loses Campaign Manager On the Road</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Goss, campaign manager for Frank L.
O'Bannon, the Indiana Democratic candidate for lieutenant governor,
probably wondered if he would ever get back from the Democratic
National Convention in Atlanta.
   Goss was riding home with O'Bannon and O'Bannon's wife, Judy, in
the couple's van when he slipped into the back of the van and fell
asleep.
   South of Chattanooga, Tenn., the O'Bannons pulled over at a rest
stop and stepped out quietly so as not to awaken Goss. While they
were in the restrooms, Goss awoke and also decided to visit the
facilities.
   When he returned, the van was gone.
   About 80 miles up the interstate, the O'Bannon's changed drivers
and discovered their passenger was missing.
   ``You don't see how you can miss each other, going into a
one-room thing like that,'' said O'Bannon.
   A call to Georgia state police produced the number of the rest
area. Goss was tracked down. He then hitched a ride up the road to
where the O'Bannons had stopped.
   ``We laughed all the way home,'' O'Bannon said Saturday.
</TEXT>
