<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Poland-Inspectors,0119</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.S. Military Inspectors Arrive to See Exercises</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four U.S. military inspectors arrived
Monday to observe military maneuvers in northwestern Poland, U.S.
officials said.
   It was the first time the United States has sent military
observers to this Warsaw Pact country under a 1986 agreement
allowing such inspections as a way of building confidence and
security in Europe.
   Ryszard Straus, of the Polish government press office in Warsaw,
said he had no further details on the location of the maneuvers. He
said the exercises were small, below the level requiring official
notification under the accord.
   The inspectors will be in Poland for 48 hours, said U.S. Embassy
spokesman Hugh Hara.
</TEXT>
