<HEAD>Four Die While Hang Gliding in Sudden Storm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LECCO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Monday recovered the bodies of
four people who were killed when their hang gliders crashed in a
sudden rainstorm at this northern Italian resort on Lake Como.
   The victims, all Italians, were caught by the storm after
jumping from Mount Cornizzolo, a favorite spot for hang gliders, on
Sunday. Three other people were injured.
