<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--FighterCrash     07-25 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Fighter Crash,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>F-16 Down Off SC Coast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Air Force F-16 jet fighter crashed
off the South Carolina coast today during a training exercise, but
the pilot ejected safely, military authorities said.
   The crash occurred at about 10:15 a.m. and the pilot was picked
up about 40 minutes later by a helicopter from the Marine Corps Air
Station in Beaufort, said Dave McMahon, a spokesman at Shaw Air
Force Base in Sumter.
   The accident happened about 50 miles off the coast, he said.
   The pilot, whose identity wasn't immediately released, was taken
to a hospital for examination, McMahon said. His condition wasn't
immediately known.
   McMahon said that a board of officers from Shaw will investigate
the cause.
   The crash was reported by another plane that was on the training
exercise with the one-seat F-16, McMahon said.
</TEXT>
