<HEAD>Princess's Mother-in-Law Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRISTOL, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ann Phillips, Princess Anne's
mother-in-law, died Monday of a pancreas ailment at the age of 62,
Buckingham Palace said.
   Mrs. Phillips was the mother of Capt. Mark Phillips, who in 1973
married Anne, the only daughter of Queen Elizabeth II.
   A palace spokesman said Phillips was at his mother's side when
she died at Southmead Hospital near her home in Wiltshire, southern
England.
   Other survivors include her husband, Maj. Peter Phillips, and
grandchildren, Peter, 10; and Zara, 7, the son and daughter of Anne
and Mark Phillips. The funeral will be private, Buckingham Palace
said.
