<HEAD>Asarco Acquires OMI for $100 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Asarco Inc., a producer of nonferrous metals,
said Monday that it will buy the specialty chemical company OMI
International Corp. for $100 million.
   The purchase, which is subject to approval by regulatory
authorities, would be made with available corporate funds, said
Richard de J. Osborne, chairman of Asarco.
   Asarco had sales of $1.4 billion in 1987, while OMI, a privately
held company based in Warren, Mich., had revenue of $153 million.
OMI acquired its business from Occidental Petroleum Corp. in 1983.
