<1ST_LINE>d f AM-AutoRecall     07-25 0135</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Recall,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Volkswagen Recalling More Than 1,000 Vehicles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Volkswagen of America Inc. said Monday it would
recall 1,050 of its 1987-88 Vanagon models because of possible
problems with tire mounting and jacks.
   Volkswagen said it voluntarily would recall 650 of its 1988
Vanagon Wolfsburg Edition models because the vehicles may have been
equipped with improper jacks. The vehicle could slip off the jack,
the Troy-based company said in a written statement.
   The company also said it was recalling 400 1987-88 model
Vanagons with alloy wheels and Semperit brand tires. The company
said improper tire mounting procedures used during the vehicle's
assembly may have caused the tire bead to crack, which could result
in a loss of air pressure.
   Volkswagen said it was unaware of any accidents related to
either recall.
</TEXT>
